# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js 15 portfolio project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 1.1.1 using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the new package and its dependencies

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag, after the ThemeProvider closing tag

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I implemented the Next.js App Router specific integration:

1. **Framework Detection**: Identified the project as Next.js 15 with App Router (based on the presence of `src/app/layout.tsx`)
2. **Package Manager**: Used npm (as indicated by the existing `package-lock.json`)
3. **Component Placement**: Added the `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag as per the documentation's recommendation for App Router projects

## Verification

All verification steps completed successfully:
- ✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
- ✅ Linter passed with no errors (`npm run lint`)
- ✅ Type checking passed during build
- ✅ No breaking changes to existing functionality

## Next Steps

To enable Speed Insights data collection:
1. Deploy this change to Vercel
2. Navigate to your Vercel dashboard
3. Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
4. Choose your project and click "Enable"
5. After the next deployment, Speed Insights will start collecting performance metrics

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package dependencies
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights component import and usage
